### 1. Valid expense under $100 -> Auto-approved
POST http://localhost:7071/api/expenses/start
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "employee_name": "Josue Muhire",
  "employee_email": "josue@example.com",
  "amount": 75,
  "category": "travel",
  "description": "Taxi from airport to client site",
  "manager_email": "manager@example.com"
}

### 2. Valid expense >= $100 -> Manager approves
POST http://localhost:7071/api/expenses/start
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "employee_name": "Josue Muhire",
  "employee_email": "josue@example.com",
  "amount": 250,
  "category": "software",
  "description": "Annual software subscription",
  "manager_email": "manager@example.com"
}

### 2b. Approve pending expense
POST http://localhost:7071/api/expenses/approve/fab80b9d0dce4de9997b93b9e508b19e

### 2c. Check approved expense status
GET http://localhost:7071/api/expenses/status/fab80b9d0dce4de9997b93b9e508b19e


### 3. Valid expense >= $100 -> Manager rejects
POST http://localhost:7071/api/expenses/start
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "employee_name": "Josue Muhire",
  "employee_email": "josue@example.com",
  "amount": 300,
  "category": "equipment",
  "description": "External monitor purchase",
  "manager_email": "manager@example.com"
}

### 3b. Reject pending expense
POST http://localhost:7071/api/expenses/reject/f2cdc84261bd485fb27b11f44c60bd55

### 3c. Check rejected expense status
GET http://localhost:7071/api/expenses/status/f2cdc84261bd485fb27b11f44c60bd55


### 4. Valid expense >= $100 -> No manager response
POST http://localhost:7071/api/expenses/start
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "employee_name": "Josue Muhire",
  "employee_email": "josue@example.com",
  "amount": 180,
  "category": "meals",
  "description": "Team dinner with client",
  "manager_email": "manager@example.com"
}

### 4b. Check escalated expense status
GET http://localhost:7071/api/expenses/status/791f781f8c0d45f5bc8eee58977c05f4


### 5. Missing required fields
POST http://localhost:7071/api/expenses/start
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "employee_name": "Josue Muhire",
  "employee_email": "josue@example.com",
  "amount": 90,
  "category": "travel",
  "description": "Taxi to airport"
}

### 5b. Check missing fields status
GET http://localhost:7071/api/expenses/status/97e376ccf8c840eb88f80ed08aca3c90


### 6. Invalid category
POST http://localhost:7071/api/expenses/start
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "employee_name": "Josue Muhire",
  "employee_email": "josue@example.com",
  "amount": 120,
  "category": "gaming",
  "description": "Game subscription reimbursement",
  "manager_email": "manager@example.com"
}

### 6b. Check invalid category status
GET http://localhost:7071/api/expenses/status/e7ca35b48a684b928460a899683d0f71